# Copy to dspm-bridge.env and edit. Read by the systemd unit.
# norns' IP on the LAN the bridge shares with it (give norns a static DHCP lease
# so this never moves). This OSC leg never crosses a Cloudflare tunnel -- the
# norns must be reachable from this box over UDP.
NORNS_HOST=192.168.8.20
NORNS_PORT=10111
BRIDGE_WS_PORT=8081
# BRIDGE_TICK_MS=40
# SESSIONS_DIR=/home/pi/dspm-archive/sessions

# ---- auto-pull the norns tape WAV into the session folder (tape-pull.js) -----
# When recording stops, the bridge scp's <name>.wav off the norns into the
# current session folder and sets manifest.tape_file. Needs passwordless SSH
# from this box to the norns -- run once:  ssh-copy-id we@$NORNS_HOST
# (default norns creds: we / sleep). Defaults shown; uncomment to override.
# NORNS_SSH_USER=we
# NORNS_TAPE_DIR=/home/we/dust/audio/tape
# TAPE_PULL=0   # set to 0 to disable auto-pull (e.g. NAT'd remote norns)

# ---- Debian box + Cloudflare named tunnel (Profile 4, see DEPLOY-DEBIAN.md) --
# Bind to loopback only: cloudflared connects locally, so nothing but the tunnel
# can reach the bridge. Leave unset (defaults 0.0.0.0) for a LAN rig that phones
# hit directly.
# BRIDGE_BIND=127.0.0.1
# Long random secret -- gates /admin/crowd (performer kill-switch) + tape
# controls from anywhere once the bridge is public. Generate: openssl rand -hex 24
# BRIDGE_ADMIN_TOKEN=CHANGE-ME-long-random-secret
